## Usage Examples

### Basic Usage
```rust
use fastmcp_console::console;

// Automatically detects agent context
let c = console();

// Print with markup (styled if rich enabled, plain otherwise)
c.print("[bold green]Success\![/] Operation completed.");

// Print plain (never styled)
c.print_plain("Debug: raw data here");

// Horizontal rule
c.rule(Some("Configuration"));

// Check if rich is enabled
if c.is_rich() {
    // Do fancy rendering
} else {
    // Use simple fallback
}
```

### With Explicit Control
```rust
// Force rich output (for debugging)
let c = FastMcpConsole::with_enabled(true);

// Force plain output (for testing)
let c = FastMcpConsole::with_enabled(false);
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Console ALWAYS writes to stderr, NEVER stdout
- [ ] is_rich() correctly reflects detection results
- [ ] print() strips markup when rich is disabled
- [ ] All renderables have plain-text fallback paths
- [ ] console() returns a static reference (no allocation per call)
- [ ] init_console() allows early initialization with explicit settings
- [ ] Works correctly with custom writers (for testing)

## Integration Points
This console will be used by:
- Banner (startup display)
- Logging (RichLogger)
- Status display (request/response)
- Error formatting
- Progress indicators
- All other rich output

